title: in case detectCores() will return NA as stated in the documentation.
body:
as stated in the [documentation](https://stat.ethz.ch/R-manual/R-devel/library/parallel/html/detectCores.html) of detectCores(), direct usage to mcapply is highly not recommended which would potentially break the code. so I add one more check in the function just in case this would happen.
Thanks for ur review.

title: Cache model result
body:
Parallel generation of models is a computationally intensive task that, as it was coded, required complete success to return any result at all.

This update caches each model as it's generated and checks for prior model existence before computing a new model. That way, a user can safely restart model generation where only new computations will be performed.

As an additional benefit, partial results can be inspected while model generation is ongoing.

digest::digest is used to create a temporary directory name based on the vocabulary.

title: Development
body:
Merging lots of changes from development version. This version makes more use of C++ and optimizes parallelization according to whether or not you're running Windows or a Unix system.

There are other, more minor, changes as well. I've also included a function that wraps lda::lda.collapsed.gibbs.sampler with nicer syntax.

title: correct exact matching method for columns that should be merged
body:
grep(......, fixed = TRUE) != an exact match; it's a substring match. 

So in your version, foo would merge: foo, foos, wonderfoo, wonderfoos, foobar, foobars, footer, footers, etc.

which(.... == .....) provides the exact match you're looking for.
